30:41.033 --> 30:43.433
And I'll take the rag back.
Thank you very much.

30:43.500 --> 30:46.500
Melanie, I'll take the rag back
and the chalkboard.

30:46.567 --> 30:51.200
Now, when they were about to communicate,
they would take a piece of chalk

30:53.633 --> 30:55.300
and slide it in between the chalkboards

30:55.367 --> 30:58.233
in case someone or something
felt like communicating.

30:58.300 --> 31:00.100
Would you mind holding on
to the chalkboard just like this?

31:00.167 --> 31:01.833
Rest them on your lap.
We'll get to them in a bit.

31:02.867 --> 31:06.033
Melanie, close your eyes.
Keep them that way till I tell you.

31:06.333 --> 31:07.900
Over the next minute or so, Melanie,

31:07.967 --> 31:11.467
I need you to concentrate on any
physical experience that happens to you.

31:11.867 --> 31:13.733
Don't be scared and don't move,

31:13.800 --> 31:18.933
but be aware of any sensation,
whether it be hot, cold, tickling,

31:19.000 --> 31:22.267
or anything else that you might feel,
and remember it.

31:45.467 --> 31:47.033
Melanie, open your eyes.
With your left hand,

31:47.100 --> 31:50.233
point to where it felt like
something touched you.

31:50.767 --> 31:53.533
