to sometimes a scream or two, you know.

33:11.533 --> 33:13.800
Penn and Teller are ready.
They've had a good talk about it.

33:13.867 --> 33:15.500
Well, you know, uh,

33:16.633 --> 33:21.300
we get asked all the time what
the hardest things to do in magic are.

33:21.367 --> 33:24.100
But one of the hardest things
to do in magic

33:24.167 --> 33:27.800
is to stand centerstage and tell a story

33:27.867 --> 33:31.333
that the audience is engaged in
and believes in.

33:31.400 --> 33:35.133
And a lot of times, we've seen
a lot of people come out

33:35.200 --> 33:38.300
and tell the story
and no one gives a damn.

33:38.600 --> 33:40.100
-(CHUCKLES)
-And you stood there,

33:40.167 --> 33:43.700
and the whole audience
was completely rapt in their attention.

33:44.167 --> 33:48.833
Now we do a trick in our show called
The Magic Bullet or The Bullet Catch,

33:48.900 --> 33:51.000
and it's one of the tricks
we're most proud of.

33:51.067 --> 33:55.933
And we got help for that trick
by a man by the name of Steve Shaw.

33:56.733 --> 33:58.567
And Steve Shaw also did

33:58.633 --> 34:03.467
something very close to the Genesis song
<i>Invisible Touch.</i>

34:03.867 --> 34:06.867
And your performance of it
was beautiful for us.

34:07.900 --> 34:11.400
We're so happy,
and this is an important thing to say,

34:11.467 --> 34:13.766
that you did that without a gimmick.

34:13.833 --> 34:16.533
You did that with real magic
and real thought,

34:16.600 --> 34:19.533
and there's people who do that same trick
with a gimmick.

34:19.600 --> 34:22.933
We don't like it as much.
You did a pure Steve Shaw,

34:23.000 --> 34:26.433
and you also did the slate routine
absolutely pure,

34:26.632 --> 34:28.600
just the way the spiritualists did it.

34:28.667 --> 34:31.733
And we loved the whole package,
and I think you know

34:31.833 --> 34:34.900
that once we've said Steve Shaw,
you probably didn't fool us,

34:35.000 --> 34:36.733
but, boy, did we love that routine.

34:36.800 --> 34:38.067
Well, thank you very much.

